title: WANTED: Woman accused of stealing cell phone from Walmart 5 hours ago
content: Source: Escambia County Sheriff's Office    PENSACOLA, Fla. (WEAR) —    Deputies are asking for your help in identifying a woman they say stolen a cell phone on May 22.    According to the Escambia County Sheriff's Office, the woman stole a Galaxy Note 5 phone with a pink case from the Walmart on Highway 29.    If you have any information contact the sheriff's office at 436-9620 or Crime Stoppers at 433-STOP.
